== The Golden Chain of Homer: Book I
_by Anton Josef Kirchweger (attributed), c. 1723 — IGF / Justitius Edition, Inner Garden Foundation, 2025_

#hm-note[
  Book I is the foundational text for the Tyro tier. It establishes the cosmological framework of the "Chain": the perpetual descent of Spirit into Matter and return of Matter into Spirit. The entire work is a running commentary on the Emerald Tablet of Hermes. The student must master the concept of *intermediaries* — the Rule that one extreme can never unite with another without a mediating middle nature — before any laboratory work will succeed. The entire book reduces to a single axiom: *"Non transiri posse ab uno extremo ad alterum extremum absque medio"* — one cannot pass from one extreme to another without an intermediary.
]

